From bdbec0485a3914c9c5f2ec13b457153de92a3899 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 10:55:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Wire fund report pages to live Supabase data instead of
 static mocks
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The admin console's 6 fund report pages (embedded via iframe in
fund-view.html, plus fund-overview.html) drifted out of sync with the
member portal despite the UI's own copy claiming they're "auto-computed" —
in reality they were hand-baked static HTML with hardcoded figures and, in
nta-history's case, a literally fake made-up chart formula.

Ports the member portal's actual live rendering stack (member-api.js's
Supabase loaders, shell.js's shared globals/chart helpers, and each page's
pgXxx() renderer) into this repo, adapted for the admin auth guard instead
of member login. fund-overview.html's previous editable form (writing to a
now-unused fund_overview table the member page no longer reads) is replaced
outright with the same read-only live dashboard the member portal shows,
per direction. shareholder-list.html keeps its existing live data and
admin-only metric cards/masking, just gains the member portal's FY-tab
dimension. statement-download.html is a visual-only port to the unified
document-list layout, since (unlike the other 5) it has no natural
single-investor data source on an admin-viewed page.

Also stages supabase/functions/fetch-historical/ (copied from the member
portal) — comparison.html's multi-index benchmark data depends on it, and
it needs a manual `supabase functions deploy fetch-historical` before that
data will load in production; not something this session can run.

